The paper discusses the use of Case-Based Reasoning (CBR) in design, which is a common topic in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of an interdisciplinary cognitive approach, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches on the organization and retrieval of cases, which could fall under the category of Cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper briefly discusses the development and evaluation of CBR systems, which could relate to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
